column1: TOTAL LOAD & WIND GENERATION IN THE BPA CONTROL AREA (Balancing Authority Area)
This data pertains to the Total Load & Total Wind, Hydro, and Thermal Generation in the BPA Balancing Authority area (control area).
It is based upon 5-minute interpolated snapshots.
The Balancing Authority load reflects the load in our electrical control area, within which our AGC systems balance generation, interchange, and load.
This is the most common building block unit for load analysis within NWPP, WECC, and NERC.
For wind plants with output split between multiple control areas (e.g., Nine Canyon) only the portion of the output in the BPA BA is included.
This file includes the Total Wind Generation "Basepoint", which is the sum of all operator-supplied wind gen forecasts (schedules).
Source: 5-min data via SCADA/PI point AGC_ONLN.CAREA..MW.103349 (Total Wind Basepoint)
Source: 5-min data via SCADA/PI point AGCDISTB.AGCRPT..MW.79687 (Total Wind Generation)
Source: 5-min data via SCADA/PI point BPA.CAREA..MW.45583 (Net Load)
Source: 5-min data via SCADA/PI point AGCDISTB.AGCRPT..MW.79682 (Total Hydro Generation)
Source: 5-min data via SCADA/PI point AGCDISTB.AGCRPT..MW.79685 (Total Thermal Generation)
Source: 5-min data via SCADA/PI point AGCDISTB.AGCRPT..MW.45581 (Net Interchange)
